</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="079613A3ABFED64D80909F27DBE23D68" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="ECF09C27F2D4535A241340405CB22F60" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="241CA4976EAB397B014D29B01B911409" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
The species in this genus are mainly associated with plants in the family 
<taxonomicName id="04B9E870FE7E724F9B1607305F420678" genus="Malvaceae" lsidName="Malvaceae" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="genus">Malvaceae</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="43CD0AF81735C6BDE776662FA87246AE" author="Jolivet, P" journalOrPublisher="An essay about the relationships between the leaf-beetles and their food-plants. Backhuys Publishers, Leiden" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" title="Host-plants of Chrysomelidae of the World." year="1995">Jolivet and Hawkeswood 1995</bibRefCitation>
: 128); some are known to cause damage to cotton crops, 
<taxonomicName id="DC67976F6C7EC6DE670824467AF0EA65" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Gossypium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gossypium" order="Malvales" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Gossypium</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName id="B3019D06CBA0B6F51991A000235BA178" genus="Malvaceae" lsidName="Malvaceae" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="genus">Malvaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="088A83B68D41EE7B04CAE8F57E3A9AD4" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="notes">
<paragraph id="122FF6DC43205644425E6C370599D70C" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4AD402BC86BFF2B3CA1EDA15AA077572" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
About fifty species are known from Sub-Saharan Africa, with one having been recorded from Madagascar. There are no significant diagnostic characters distinguishing 
<taxonomicName id="533BC1C40E09A7036D6542363C1AC8CE" authority="Csiki, 1940" authorityName="Csiki" authorityYear="1940" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Podagricina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Podagricina" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Podagricina</taxonomicName>
Csiki from 
<taxonomicName id="75E936B56AE29EA8B8B2A2FC6B5540A6" authority="Chevrolat, 1836" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1836" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Podagrica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Podagrica" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Podagrica</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, the following new synonymy is proposed: 
<taxonomicName id="23B930931AB609BBB07A694B9F957417" authority="Chevrolat, 1836" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1836" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Podagrica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Podagrica" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Podagrica</taxonomicName>
Chevrolat, 1836 = 
<taxonomicName id="FE245570CAF019879E269D9531E0DB4A" authority="Csiki, 1940" authorityName="Csiki" authorityYear="1940" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Podagricina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Podagricina" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Podagricina</taxonomicName>
Csiki in Heikertinger and Csiki, 1940 syn. n. Type material examined: 
<taxonomicName id="443FB106F7736A1E624CBB47C9B50473" authority="Chevrolat, 1837" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Balanomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Balanomorpha aethiopica" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aethiopica">Balanomorpha aethiopica</taxonomicName>
Chapuis, &quot;Bogos, 1870, Keren, O. Beccari&quot;, 4 syntypes (MCSN).
</paragraph>
